---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const REPO_URL = 'https://github.com/sSolal/elu4';
---

<Base
  title="Open Source — Elua"
  description="Elua is an open-source game and an open world. The core game is authored by us; the world around it grows with the people who build inside it."
>
  <!-- HERO ------------------------------------------------------------ -->
  <section class="ohero section-pad">
    <div class="wrap ohero__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Open source</p>
      <h1>A world built in the open,<br />and meant to be added to</h1>
      <p class="lede ohero__lede">
        Elua is open source. The core game is authored and kept by us — but the
        world doesn’t stop at its edges. User-created assets, subworlds, annex
        arcs and quests, even new mechanics, can all be folded into our open
        world.
      </p>
      <div class="ohero__row">
        <a class="btn" href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">View the source on GitHub →</a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="#contribute">How contributions work</a>
      </div>
      <p class="muted ohero__early">
        This is early. The repository, the tools, and the process are all still
        taking shape — what follows is the shape we’re building toward.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHY OPEN -------------------------------------------------------- -->
  <section class="section-pad band">
    <div class="wrap two">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Why open</p>
        <h2>An authored heart, an open world around it</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="two__body">
        <p>
          The main game — Tessara, the keeper’s story, the world you set right —
          is hand-crafted, and we keep it that way. It’s the part we author with
          care, so it holds together.
        </p>
        <p>
          But a single team can only build so much world. Everything that grows
          around that authored heart can be made by the people who play: places
          to explore, stories to tell, even new ways to play.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TWO LAYERS ------------------------------------------------------ -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">One world, two halves</p>
      <h2 class="layers__h">The part we author, and the part we build together</h2>
      <div class="layers">
        <article class="layer panel">
          <h3>The core</h3>
          <p class="layer__tag muted">Authored · curated by us</p>
          <p>
            Tessara and the keeper’s story: the world we hand-craft and keep
            coherent. This is the great game, and it stays curated.
          </p>
        </article>
        <article class="layer panel layer--weave">
          <h3>The open world</h3>
          <p class="layer__tag muted">Open · built together</p>
          <p>
            Everything growing around the core — assets, subworlds, side-arcs,
            quests, even new mechanics — made by people like you and woven into
            the same living world for anyone to reach.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW CONTRIBUTIONS GET IN --------------------------------------- -->
  <section id="contribute" class="section-pad band">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">How contributions work</p>
      <h2 class="pub__h">Build something, and we’ll weave it in</h2>
      <p class="lede pub__lede">
        The idea is simple: what you make can become part of the world everyone
        plays in.
      </p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li class="step">
          <span class="step__n">1</span>
          <div>
            <h3>You build something</h3>
            <p class="muted">
              An asset, a subworld, a side-arc, a quest, a puzzle — even a new
              mechanic. Anything that belongs in the world.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step">
          <span class="step__n">2</span>
          <div>
            <h3>You share it with us</h3>
            <p class="muted">
              Open it up and send it our way. It’s open source, so working in
              the open is the natural way to do it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="step">
          <span class="step__n">3</span>
          <div>
            <h3>The good ones get woven in</h3>
            <p class="muted">
              What fits the world and holds together becomes part of Elua — out
              where everyone can find it and explore it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <p class="muted abstract-note">
        We’re keeping this light for now — we’re not there yet. The concrete
        tools and review process will firm up as the core game does, and we’d
        rather figure them out in the open, with you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNDER THE HOOD -------------------------------------------------- -->
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Under the hood</p>
      <h2 class="hood__h">For the engine-curious</h2>
      <div class="hood">
        {
          [
            ['C++17', 'A from-scratch engine — no off-the-shelf 3D engine could hold a fourth coordinate in its bones.'],
            ['Rotor4D', 'Rotation handled with geometric algebra — planes, not axes, so all six rotation planes compose cleanly in 4D.'],
            ['OpenGL pipeline', 'A real-time 4D → 3D → 2D projection renderer with depth cues, occlusion, and a tunable look.'],
            ['VR-ready', 'An optional OpenXR path — four dimensions read even better with stereo depth and your own head as the camera.'],
            ['Headless tools', 'A CLI for reasoning about 4D scenes and generating geometry, so the math can be tested without a window.'],
            ['Open by default', 'Built to be read, run, and extended — the same systems we build the world with are the ones we mean to open up.'],
          ].map(([k, v]) => (
            <div class="hood__cell">
              <code class="hood__k">{k}</code>
              <p class="muted">{v}</p>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GET INVOLVED ---------------------------------------------------- -->
  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="wrap cta">
      <h2>Join us in the adventure</h2>
      <p class="lede">
        Elua is an open source project, maintained and fixed by a few motivated
        menders. It’s early, and that’s the best time to arrive. Watch the
        source, follow along, and say hello — feel free to contact us, or join
        us in the adventure.
      </p>
      <div class="cta__row">
        <a class="btn" href={REPO_URL} rel="noopener">Star &amp; watch on GitHub</a>
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/dimension">Four dimensions?</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .band {
    border-block: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(11, 16, 25, 0.5), transparent 60%);
  }

  /* hero */
  .ohero__inner {
    max-width: 52rem;
  }
  .ohero h1 {
    font-size: var(--step-4);
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }
  .ohero__lede {
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
    max-width: 46ch;
  }
  .ohero__row {
    margin-top: 2.2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }
  .ohero__early {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    max-width: 52ch;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* two-col */
  .two {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.6rem 3rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  }
  @media (min-width: 860px) {
    .two {
      grid-template-columns: 0.9fr 1.1fr;
      align-items: start;
    }
  }
  .two h2 {
    max-width: 16ch;
  }
  .two__body p + p {
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
  }

  /* layers */
  .layers__h {
    max-width: 22ch;
    margin-bottom: 2.4rem;
  }
  .layers {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.2rem;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    align-items: stretch;
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .layers {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }
  .layer {
    padding: 1.8rem;
  }
  .layer h3 {
    color: var(--lamp-300);
  }
  .layer--weave h3 {
    color: var(--drift-400);
  }
  .layer__tag {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-block: 0.3rem 0.9rem;
  }

  /* publishing steps */
  .pub__h {
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }
  .pub__lede {
    max-width: 52ch;
    margin-bottom: 2.4rem;
  }
  .steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
    gap: 1.4rem;
    padding-block: 1.6rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .step:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .step__n {
    display: grid;
    place-content: center;
    width: 2.4rem;
    height: 2.4rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent);
    color: var(--lamp-300);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 0 18px -6px rgba(227, 168, 87, 0.6);
  }
  .step h3 {
    color: var(--ceramic-100);
  }
  .step p {
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    font-size: var(--step-0);
  }
  .abstract-note {
    margin-top: 1.8rem;
    max-width: 60ch;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }

  /* under the hood */
  .hood__h {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .hood {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 16rem), 1fr));
  }
  .hood__cell {
    padding: 1.3rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line-700);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: rgba(11, 16, 25, 0.4);
  }
  .hood__k {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--lamp-300);
    background: rgba(36, 50, 70, 0.5);
    padding: 0.18em 0.5em;
    border-radius: 5px;
  }
  .hood__cell p {
    margin-top: 0.7rem;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }

  /* cta */
  .cta-band {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background:
      radial-gradient(70% 120% at 50% 0%, rgba(227, 168, 87, 0.1), transparent 60%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(11, 16, 25, 0.4), transparent);
    padding-block: clamp(4rem, 10vw, 7rem);
  }
  .cta {
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 50rem;
  }
  .cta .lede {
    margin: 1.2rem auto 2rem;
    max-width: 52ch;
  }
  .cta__row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }
</style>
